swL2MgmtMIB.name: swL2MgmtMIB
swL2MgmtMIB.description: The Structure of Layer 2 Network Management Information.

IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits.name: IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits
IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits.description: This data type is used as the syntax of the swL2PortAutoNegCapabilityBits, swL2PortAutoNegCapAdvertisedBits, and swL2PortAutoNegCapReceivedBits objects in swL2PortAutoNegTable.

swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort.name: swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort
swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort.description: The number of ports within this switch. This value is the sum of the ports within this switch.

swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse.name: swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse
swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse.description: The number of ports in this switch connected to the segment or the end stations.

swDevModuleInfoTable.name: swDevModuleInfoTable
swDevModuleInfoTable.description: This table contains the module information.

swDevModuleInfoEntry.name: swDevModuleInfoEntry
swDevModuleInfoEntry.description: A list of management information for each unit in the system.

swDevModuleInfoUnitID.name: swDevModuleInfoUnitID
swDevModuleInfoUnitID.description: This object indicates the specific unit ID in the stacking/chassis table.

swDevModuleInfoModuleID.name: swDevModuleInfoModuleID
swDevModuleInfoModuleID.description: This object indicates the module ID of this unit.

swDevModuleInfoModuleName.name: swDevModuleInfoModuleName
swDevModuleInfoModuleName.description: A textual string containing name of the the module.

swDevModuleInfoReversion.name: swDevModuleInfoReversion
swDevModuleInfoReversion.description: A textual string containing reversion of the module.

swDevModuleInfoSerial.name: swDevModuleInfoSerial
swDevModuleInfoSerial.description: A textual string containing serial of the module.

swDevModuleInfoDescription.name: swDevModuleInfoDescription
swDevModuleInfoDescription.description: A textual string containing description of the module.

swDevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus.name: swDevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus
swDevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus.description: This object is a set of system LED indications. The first two octets is defined as system LED. The first LED is power LED. The second LED is console LED. The third LED is RPS (Redundancy Power Supply) LED. The other octets following the second octets are the logical port LED (following dot1dBasePort ordering). Every two bytes are presented to a port. The first byte is presentd to the Link/Activity LED. The second byte is presented to the Speed LED. Link/Activity LED : The most significant bit is used for blink/solid: 8 = The LED blinks. The second significant bit is used for link status: 1 = link fail. 2 = link pass. Speed LED : 01 = 10Mbps. 02 = 100Mbps. 03 = 1000Mbps. 04 = 10Gbps. The four remaining bits are currently unused and must be 0.

swL2DevCtrlStpState.name: swL2DevCtrlStpState
swL2DevCtrlStpState.description: This object can be enabled or disabled spanning tree algorithm during runtime of the system.

swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.name: swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping
swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.description: This object indicates layer 2 Internet Group Management Protocol (IGMP) capture function is enabled or disabled.

swL2DevCtrlRmonState.name: swL2DevCtrlRmonState
swL2DevCtrlRmonState.description: This object can be enabled or disabled RMON.

swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.name: swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter
swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.description: As the object is set to active, all the statistic counters will be cleared. If set to normal, do nothing.

swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl.name: swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl
swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl.description: Indicates the VLAN ID which the Dot1dTpFdbTable belongs to ; The default value is DEFAULT-VLAN-ID of system .

swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId.name: swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId
swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId.description: This object controls which Vlan includes system ip. And the Vlan should have been created.

swL2MACNotifyState.name: swL2MACNotifyState
swL2MACNotifyState.description: This object can enabled or disabled MAC Notification.

swL2MACNotifyHistorySize.name: swL2MACNotifyHistorySize
swL2MACNotifyHistorySize.description: This object indicates the history size of variation MAC in address table. The default value is 1 .

swL2MACNotifyInterval.name: swL2MACNotifyInterval
swL2MACNotifyInterval.description: This object indicates the time interval in second for trigger the MAC notify message.

swL2DevCtrlWebTcpPort.name: swL2DevCtrlWebTcpPort
swL2DevCtrlWebTcpPort.description: This object can designate tcp port. When web disable this object can't accessible.

swL2DevCtrlTelnetTcpPort.name: swL2DevCtrlTelnetTcpPort
swL2DevCtrlTelnetTcpPort.description: This object can designate tcp port. When telnet disable this object can't accessible.

swL2DevCtrlLedPOEState.name: swL2DevCtrlLedPOEState
swL2DevCtrlLedPOEState.description: When set enabled(1), the POE LED is lighten. When set disabled(2), the Link/ACT/Speed LED is lighten.

swL2DevCtrlLLDPState.name: swL2DevCtrlLLDPState
swL2DevCtrlLLDPState.description: Specifies the state of the LLDP function. When this function is enabled, the switch can start to transmit LLDP packets and receive and process the LLDP packets. The specific function of each port will depend on the per port LLDP setting. For the advertisement of LLDP packets, the switch announces the information to its neighbor through ports. For receiving LLDP packets, the switch will learn the information from the LLDP packets advertised from the neighbor in the neighbor table.

swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState.name: swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState
swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState.description: When lldp is disabled and lldp forward-message's are enabled, the LLDP Data Unit packets received by the switch will be forwarded.

swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState.name: swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState
swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState.description: This indicates the global state of the VLAN trunking feature of the device.

swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.name: swL2DevAlarmNewRoot
swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.description: When the device has become the new root of the Spanning Tree, this object decide whether to send a new root trap.

swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.name: swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange
swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.description: This object determine to send a trap or not when the switch topology was changed. If the object is enabled(3), the topologyChange trap is sent by the device when any of its configured ports transitions from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. For the same port tranition, the device doesn't send the trap if this object value is disabled or other.

swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.name: swL2DevAlarmLinkChange
swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.description: This object determine to send a trap or not when the link was changed. If the object is enabled(3), the Link Change trap is sent by the device when any of its ports link change. The device doesn't send the trap if this object value is disabled or other.

swL2MultiFilterTable.name: swL2MultiFilterTable
swL2MultiFilterTable.description: A table that contains infomation about vlan multicast filter mode.

swL2MultiFilterEntry.name: swL2MultiFilterEntry
swL2MultiFilterEntry.description: A list of multicast filter mode information for each vlan.

swL2PortInfoTable.name: swL2PortInfoTable
swL2PortInfoTable.description: A table that contains information about every port.

swL2PortInfoEntry.name: swL2PortInfoEntry
swL2PortInfoEntry.description: A list of information for each port of the device.

swL2PortInfoPortIndex.name: swL2PortInfoPortIndex
swL2PortInfoPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortInfoMediumType.name: swL2PortInfoMediumType
swL2PortInfoMediumType.description: Indicates medium type of the port number.

swL2PortInfoUnitID.name: swL2PortInfoUnitID
swL2PortInfoUnitID.description: Indicates ID of the unit in the system

swL2PortInfoType.name: swL2PortInfoType
swL2PortInfoType.description: This object indicates the connector type of this port.

swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.name: swL2PortInfoLinkStatus
swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.description: This object indicates the port link status.

swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.name: swL2PortInfoNwayStatus
swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.description: This object indicates the port speed and duplex mode.

swL2PortInfoErrDisReason.name: swL2PortInfoErrDisReason
swL2PortInfoErrDisReason.description: This object indicates the port if disabled and why error disabled.

swL2PortCtrlTable.name: swL2PortCtrlTable
swL2PortCtrlTable.description: A table that contains control information about every port.

swL2PortCtrlEntry.name: swL2PortCtrlEntry
swL2PortCtrlEntry.description: A list of control information for each port of the device.

swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2PortCtrlPortIndex
swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortCtrlMediumType.name: swL2PortCtrlMediumType
swL2PortCtrlMediumType.description: Indicates medium type of the port number.

swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex.name: swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex
swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex.description: Indicates ID of the unit in the device

swL2PortCtrlAdminState.name: swL2PortCtrlAdminState
swL2PortCtrlAdminState.description: This object decide the port enabled or disabled.

swL2PortCtrlNwayState.name: swL2PortCtrlNwayState
swL2PortCtrlNwayState.description: Chose the port speed, duplex mode, and N-Way function mode.

swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.name: swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState
swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.description: The flow control mechanism is different between full duplex mode and half duplex mode. For half duplex mode, the jamming signal is asserted. For full duplex mode, IEEE 802.3x flow control function sends PAUSE frames and receives PAUSE frames.

swL2PortCtrlLockState.name: swL2PortCtrlLockState
swL2PortCtrlLockState.description: This object decide the port is locked or not.

swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState.name: swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState
swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState.description: This object set each port MAC notification state.

swL2PortCtrlAutoNegRestart.name: swL2PortCtrlAutoNegRestart
swL2PortCtrlAutoNegRestart.description: If the value of this object is set to restart(1) then this will force auto-negotiation to begin link renegotiation. If auto-negotiation signaling is disabled, a write to this object has no effect. Setting the value of this object to norestart(2) has no effect.

swL2PortCtrlAutoNegCapAdvertisedBits.name: swL2PortCtrlAutoNegCapAdvertisedBits
swL2PortCtrlAutoNegCapAdvertisedBits.description: A value that uniquely identifies the set of capabilities advertised by the local auto-negotiation entity. Capabilities in this object that are not available in swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapabilityBits cannot be enabled. Note that the local auto-negotiation entity may advertise some capabilities beyond the scope of this MIB. This is indicated by returning the bit value bOther in addition to any bit values for standard capabilities that are listed in the IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits TC.

swL2PortCtrlJumboFrame.name: swL2PortCtrlJumboFrame
swL2PortCtrlJumboFrame.description: This object configure the switch's jumbo frame settings.

swL2PortCtrlJumboFrameMaxSize.name: swL2PortCtrlJumboFrameMaxSize
swL2PortCtrlJumboFrameMaxSize.description: This object configure the switch's jumbo frame settings.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoTable.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoTable
swL2PortAutoNegInfoTable.description: A table that contains information about every port's auto negotiation status.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoEntry.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoEntry
swL2PortAutoNegInfoEntry.description: A list of information for each port auto negotiation of the device.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoPortIndex.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoPortIndex
swL2PortAutoNegInfoPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortAutoNegInfoAdminStatus.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoAdminStatus
swL2PortAutoNegInfoAdminStatus.description: If the value of this object is disabled(2) then the interface will act as it would if it had no auto-negotiation signaling. The status is affect by setting swL2PortCtrlNwayState.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapabilityBits.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapabilityBits
swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapabilityBits.description: A value that uniquely identifies the set of capabilities of the local auto-negotiation entity. Note that interfaces that support this MIB may have capabilities that extend beyond the scope of this MIB. Note that the local auto-negotiation entity may support some capabilities beyond the scope of this MIB. This is indicated by returning the bit value bOther in addition to any bit values for standard capabilities that are listed in the IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits TC.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapAdvertisedBits.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapAdvertisedBits
swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapAdvertisedBits.description: A value that uniquely identifies the set of capabilities advertised by the local auto-negotiation entity. Capabilities in this object that are not available in swL2PortAutoNegCapabilityBits cannot be enabled. Note that the local auto-negotiation entity may advertise some capabilities beyond the scope of this MIB. This is indicated by returning the bit value bOther in addition to any bit values for standard capabilities that are listed in the IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits TC.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapReceivedBits.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapReceivedBits
swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapReceivedBits.description: A value that uniquely identifies the set of capabilities received from the remote auto-negotiation entity. Note that interfaces that support this MIB may be attached to remote auto-negotiation entities that have capabilities beyond the scope of this MIB. This is indicated by returning the bit value bOther in addition to any bit values for standard capabilities that are listed in the IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits TC.

swL2PortDropCounterTable.name: swL2PortDropCounterTable
swL2PortDropCounterTable.description: A table that contains information for each port drop counter.

swL2PortDropCounterEntry.name: swL2PortDropCounterEntry
swL2PortDropCounterEntry.description: A list of information for each port auto negotiation of the device.

swL2PortDropCounterPortIndex.name: swL2PortDropCounterPortIndex
swL2PortDropCounterPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortBufferFullDrops.name: swL2PortBufferFullDrops
swL2PortBufferFullDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded while buffer full.

swL2PortACLDrops.name: swL2PortACLDrops
swL2PortACLDrops.description: The total number of packets denied by ACLs.

swL2PortMulticastDrops.name: swL2PortMulticastDrops
swL2PortMulticastDrops.description: The total number of multicast packet that is discarded.

swL2PortVLANIngressDrops.name: swL2PortVLANIngressDrops
swL2PortVLANIngressDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded by VLAN ingress checking.

swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry.name: swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry
swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOSBandwidthControlTable.

swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate.description: Indicates RX Rate(1kbit/sec) of the specifed port. Value 10000000 means no limit.

swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate.description: Indicates TX Rate(1kbit/sec) of the specifed port. Value 10000000 means no limit.

swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate.description: The Rx Rate value comes from the RADIUS server, If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the locally configured Rx Rate.

swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate.description: The Tx Rate value comes from the RADIUS server, If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the locally configured Tx Rate.

swL2QOSSchedulingEntry.name: swL2QOSSchedulingEntry
swL2QOSSchedulingEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOSSchedulingTable.

swL2QOSSchedulingMaxPkts.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMaxPkts
swL2QOSSchedulingMaxPkts.description: Indicates the maximum number of packets the hardware priority queue will be allowed to transmit before allowing the next lowest priority queue to transmit its packets. a value between 0 and 15 can be specified.

swL2QOSSchedulingMechanism.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMechanism
swL2QOSSchedulingMechanism.description: Indicates the mechanism of QOS scheduling.

swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismEffec.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismEffec
swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismEffec.description: Indicates the effective mechanism of QoS scheduling. If the swQoSSchedulingWeight is configured to be 0, then this object will always display strict (1).

swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry.name: swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry
swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityTable.

swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass.name: swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass
swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has four hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority) and 6 (the highest priority).

swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry.name: swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry
swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityTable.

swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority.name: swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority
swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority.description: The priority value to assign to untagged packets received by the switch ports on the switch..

swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority.name: swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority
swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority.description: Indicates the value of 802.1p comes from RADIUS server. If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the local configured value.

swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl
swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl.description: This object can control QOS scheduling Mechanism.

swCosBandwidthControlTable.name: swCosBandwidthControlTable
swCosBandwidthControlTable.description: A table that contains information about CoS Bandwidth Control on each port.

swCosBandwidthControlEntry.name: swCosBandwidthControlEntry
swCosBandwidthControlEntry.description: A list that contains CoS Bandwidth Control information for each port.

swCosBandwidthPort.name: swCosBandwidthPort
swCosBandwidthPort.description: This object indicates the port number.

swCosBandwidthMinRate.name: swCosBandwidthMinRate
swCosBandwidthMinRate.description: Indicates the Minimum Rate of the specified port. A value of 0 means no limit.

swCosBandwidthMaxRate.name: swCosBandwidthMaxRate
swCosBandwidthMaxRate.description: Indicates the Maximum Rate of the specified port. A value of 0 means no limit.

swCpuRxRateControlTable.name: swCpuRxRateControlTable
swCpuRxRateControlTable.description: A table that contains information about CPU receiving rate control.

swCpuRxRateControlEntry.name: swCpuRxRateControlEntry
swCpuRxRateControlEntry.description: A list that contains CPU CoS receiving rate control information.

swCpuRxClassID.name: swCpuRxClassID
swCpuRxClassID.description: Indicates the Class of Service ID.

swCpuRxRateControlStatus.name: swCpuRxRateControlStatus
swCpuRxRateControlStatus.description: Indicates the status of receiving rate control.

swL2PortSecurityControlTable.name: swL2PortSecurityControlTable
swL2PortSecurityControlTable.description: port security feature which controls the address leaning capability and the traffic forwarding decision. Each port can have this function enabled or disabled. When it is enabled and a number is given said N, which allows N addresses to be learned at this port, the first N learned addresses are locked at this port as static entry. When the learned addresses number reach N, any coming packet with not learned source addresses are discarded (e.g. dropped) and no more new addresses can be learned at this port.

swL2PortSecurityControlEntry.name: swL2PortSecurityControlEntry
swL2PortSecurityControlEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2PortSecurityControlTable.

swL2PortSecurityPortIndex.name: swL2PortSecurityPortIndex
swL2PortSecurityPortIndex.description: Indicates the secured port to lock address learning.

swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.name: swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr
swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.description: Indicates allowable number of addresses to be learned at this port.

swL2PortSecurityMode.name: swL2PortSecurityMode
swL2PortSecurityMode.description: Indicates the mode of locking address. In deleteOnTimeout(3) mode - the locked addresses can be aged out after aging timer expire. In this mode, when the locked address is aged out, the number of address can be learned has to be increased by one. In deleteOnReset(4) mode - never age out the locked addresses unless restart the system to prevent from port movement or intrusion.

swL2PortSecurityAdmState.name: swL2PortSecurityAdmState
swL2PortSecurityAdmState.description: Indicates administration state of locking address.

swL2PortSecurityDelPort.name: swL2PortSecurityDelPort
swL2PortSecurityDelPort.description: Indicates the port.0 indicated the function isn't working now.

swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.name: swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries
swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.description: Maximum number of entries in the trunk configuration table (swL2TrunkCtrlTable).

swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.name: swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries
swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.description: Current actived number of entries in the trunk configuration table.

swL2TrunkCtrlTable.name: swL2TrunkCtrlTable
swL2TrunkCtrlTable.description: This table specifys which ports group a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.name: swL2TrunkCtrlEntry
swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.description: A list of information specifies which ports group a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkIndex.name: swL2TrunkIndex
swL2TrunkIndex.description: The index of logical port trunk. The trunk group number depend on the existence of unit and module.

swL2TrunkMasterPort.name: swL2TrunkMasterPort
swL2TrunkMasterPort.description: The object indicates the master port number of the port trunk entry. When using Port Trunk, you can not configure the other ports of the group except the master port. Their configuration must be same as the master port (e.g. speed, duplex, enabled/disabled, flow control, and so on).

swL2TrunkMember.name: swL2TrunkMember
swL2TrunkMember.description: Indicate how many number of ports is included in this Trunk. The trunk port number depend on the existence of module. The maximum number of ports is 8 for one trunks.

swL2TrunkFloodingPort.name: swL2TrunkFloodingPort
swL2TrunkFloodingPort.description: The object indicates the flooding port number of the port trunk entry. The first port of the trunk is implicitly configured to be the flooding port.

swL2TrunkType.name: swL2TrunkType
swL2TrunkType.description: This object indicated that type of the trunk group. static : is static trunk group lacp : is LACP trunk group .

swL2TrunkState.name: swL2TrunkState
swL2TrunkState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2TrunkActivePorts.name: swL2TrunkActivePorts
swL2TrunkActivePorts.description: The object indicates the active ports of the port trunk entry.

swL2TrunkAlgorithm.name: swL2TrunkAlgorithm
swL2TrunkAlgorithm.description: This object configures to part of the packet examined by the switch when selecting the egress port for transmitting load-sharing data.

swL2TrunkLACPPortTable.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortTable
swL2TrunkLACPPortTable.description: This table specifys which ports group a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry
swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry.description: A list of information specifies which ports group a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex
swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex.description: The index of logical port lacp.

swL2TrunkLACPPortState.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortState
swL2TrunkLACPPortState.description: The state of logical port lacp.

swL2TrunkVLANTable.name: swL2TrunkVLANTable
swL2TrunkVLANTable.description: This table is used to manage the VLAN trunking feature of the device.

swL2TrunkVLANEntry.name: swL2TrunkVLANEntry
swL2TrunkVLANEntry.description: This object is used to configure the VLAN trunking settings for each port.

swL2TrunkVLANPort.name: swL2TrunkVLANPort
swL2TrunkVLANPort.description: This object indicates the port being configured.

swL2TrunkVLANState.name: swL2TrunkVLANState
swL2TrunkVLANState.description: The state of the logical port LACP.

swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.name: swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort
swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.description: This object indicates switch which port will sniff another port. A trunk port member cannot be configured as a target Snooping port. The port number is the sequential (logical) number which is also applied to bridge MIB, etc.

swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress
swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.description: The represent the ingress into the source port packet to sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress
swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.description: The represent the egress from the source port packet to sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortState.name: swL2MirrorPortState
swL2MirrorPortState.description: This object indicates the port mirroring state. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disabled(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. enabled(3) - this entry is reside in the table.

swL2MirrorGroupTable.name: swL2MirrorGroupTable
swL2MirrorGroupTable.description: This table specifies information about the Mirror group configuration.

swL2MirrorGroupEntry.name: swL2MirrorGroupEntry
swL2MirrorGroupEntry.description: A list of information about each Mirror group configuration.

swL2MirrorGroupID.name: swL2MirrorGroupID
swL2MirrorGroupID.description: This object indicates the mirror group. The range of this object is (1..n), the value of n depends on detail project.

swL2MirrorGroupRowStatus.name: swL2MirrorGroupRowStatus
swL2MirrorGroupRowStatus.description: This object manages this mirror group entry.

swL2MirrorGroupState.name: swL2MirrorGroupState
swL2MirrorGroupState.description: This object indicates the mirror group state.

swL2MirrorGroupLogicTargetPort.name: swL2MirrorGroupLogicTargetPort
swL2MirrorGroupLogicTargetPort.description: This object indicates the mirror group target port.

swL2MirrorGroupPortSourceIngress.name: swL2MirrorGroupPortSourceIngress
swL2MirrorGroupPortSourceIngress.description: This object indicates the mirror group ingress source ports.

swL2MirrorGroupPortSourceEngress.name: swL2MirrorGroupPortSourceEngress
swL2MirrorGroupPortSourceEngress.description: This object indicates the mirror group engress source ports.

swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.name: swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans
swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.description: Maximum number of Vlans in the layer 2 IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan.name: swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan
swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan.description: Maximum number of multicast ip group per Vlan in the layer 2 IGMP information table (swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable).

swL2IGMPCtrlTable.name: swL2IGMPCtrlTable
swL2IGMPCtrlTable.description: The table controls the Vlan's IGMP function. Its scale depends on current VLAN state (swL2VlanInfoStatus). If VLAN is disabled mode, there is only one entry in the table, with index 1. If VLAN is in Port-Base or 802.1q mode, the number of entries can be up to 12, with index range from 1 to 12.

swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.name: swL2IGMPCtrlEntry
swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.description: The entry in IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable). The entry is effective only when IGMP capture switch (swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping) is enabled.

swL2IGMPCtrlVid.name: swL2IGMPCtrlVid
swL2IGMPCtrlVid.description: This object indicates the IGMP control entry's VLAN id. If VLAN is disabled, the Vid is always 0 and cannot be changed by management users. If VLAN is in Port-Base mode, the Vid is arranged from 1 to 12, fixed form. If VLAN is in 802.1q mode, the Vid setting can vary from 1 to 4094 by management user, and the Vid in each entry must be unique in the IGMP Control Table.

swL2IGMPQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPQueryInterval
swL2IGMPQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP Host-Query packets are transmitted on this switch.

swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.name: swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime
swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.description: The maximum query response time on this switch.

swL2IGMPRobustness.name: swL2IGMPRobustness
swL2IGMPRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses.

swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval
swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages.

swL2IGMPHostTimeout.name: swL2IGMPHostTimeout
swL2IGMPHostTimeout.description: The timer value for sending IGMP query packet when none was sent by the host in the LAN. The timer works in per-VLAN basis. Our device will be activated to send the query message if the timer is expired. Please reference RFC2236-1997.

swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.name: swL2IGMPRouteTimeout
swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.description: The Router Timeout is how long a host must wait after hearing a Query before it may send any IGMPv2 messages.

swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.name: swL2IGMPLeaveTimer
swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.description: When a querier receives a Leave Group message for a group that has group members on the reception interface, it sends Group-Specific Queries every swL2IGMPLeaveTimer to the group being left.

swL2IGMPQueryState.name: swL2IGMPQueryState
swL2IGMPQueryState.description: This object decide the IGMP query enabled or disabled.

swL2IGMPCurrentState.name: swL2IGMPCurrentState
swL2IGMPCurrentState.description: This object indicates the current IGMP query state.

swL2IGMPCtrlState.name: swL2IGMPCtrlState
swL2IGMPCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disable(2) - IGMP funtion is disabled for this entry. enable(3) - IGMP funtion is enabled for this entry.

swL2IGMPFastLeaveState.name: swL2IGMPFastLeaveState
swL2IGMPFastLeaveState.description: This object indicates the fast-leave status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disable(2) - IGMP fast-leave funtion is disabled for this entry. enable(3) - IGMP fast-leave funtion is enabled for this entry.

swL2IGMPQueryVersion.name: swL2IGMPQueryVersion
swL2IGMPQueryVersion.description: Configure the IGMP version of query packet which will be sent by the router.

swL2IGMPReportSuppression.name: swL2IGMPReportSuppression
swL2IGMPReportSuppression.description: When enabled, multiple IGMP reports or leaves for a specific group (S,G) will be integrated into only one report before being sent to the router port.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable
swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.description: The table contains the number current IGMP query packets which is captured by this device, as well as the IGMP query packets sent by the device.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry
swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP query information, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled.

swL2IGMPInfoVid.name: swL2IGMPInfoVid
swL2IGMPInfoVid.description: This object indicates the Vid of associated IGMP info table entry. It follows swL2IGMPCtrlVid in the associated entry of IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.description: This object indicates the number of query packets received since the IGMP function enabled, in per-VLAN basis.

swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.description: This object indicates the send count of IGMP query messages, in per-VLAN basis. In case of IGMP timer expiration, the switch sends IGMP query packets to related VLAN member ports and increment this object by 1.

swL2IGMPInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPInfoTable
swL2IGMPInfoTable.description: The table containing current IGMP information which captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled. Note that the priority of IGMP table entries is lower than Filtering Table, i.e. if there is a table hash collision between the entries of IGMP Table and Filtering Table inside the switch H/W address table, then Filtering Table entry overwrite the colliding entry of IGMP Table. See swL2FilterMgmt description also.

swL2IGMPInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPInfoEntry
swL2IGMPInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP information which captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled.

swL2IGMPVid.name: swL2IGMPVid
swL2IGMPVid.description: This object indicates the Vid of individual IGMP table entry. It shows the Vid of IGMP report information captured on network.

swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.name: swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr
swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.description: This object is identify group ip address which is captured from IGMP packet, in per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPMacAddr.name: swL2IGMPMacAddr
swL2IGMPMacAddr.description: This object is identify mac address which is corresponding to swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr, in per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPPortMap.name: swL2IGMPPortMap
swL2IGMPPortMap.description: This object indicates which ports are belong to the same multicast group, in per-Vlan basis. Each multicast group has a octect string to indicate with port map. The most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'(Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant). The 4 octets is represent one unit port according its logic port. If the unit less 32 port, the other port don't care just fill zero.

swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount.name: swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount
swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount.description: This object indicate how much report packet was receive by our device corresponding with this entry from IGMP function enabled, in per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPRouterPortsTable.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortsTable
swL2IGMPRouterPortsTable.description: The table controls the Vlan's IGMP router ports function.

swL2IGMPRouterPortsEntry.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortsEntry
swL2IGMPRouterPortsEntry.description: The entry in IGMP router ports table (swL2IGMPRouterPortsTable).

swL2IGMPRouterPortsVid.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortsVid
swL2IGMPRouterPortsVid.description: This object indicates the IGMP router ports entry's VLAN id. If VLAN is disabled, the Vid is always 0 and cannot be changed by management users. If VLAN is in Port-Base mode, the Vid is arranged from 1 to 12, fixed form. If VLAN is in 802.1q mode, the Vid setting can vary from 1 to 4094 by management user, and the Vid in each entry must be unique in the IGMP ports Table.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTable.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTable
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTable.description: The information of the IGMP snooping multicast vlan table.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanid.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanid
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanid.description: This object indicates the vlan id of the IGMP snooping multicast vlan entry.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanName.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanName
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanName.description: This object indicates the vlan name of the IGMP snooping multicast vlan entry.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanSourcePort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanSourcePort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanSourcePort.description: This object indicate the portlist of the source ports of IGMP snooping multicast vlan. The source ports will be set as tag ports of the vlan entry. And the IGMP control messages received from the member ports would be forwarded to the source ports.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanMemberPort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanMemberPort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanMemberPort.description: This object indicate the portlist of the member ports of IGMP snooping multicast vlan. The source ports will be set as untag ports of the vlan entry. And the IGMP control messages received from the member ports would be forwarded to the source ports.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplaceSourceIP.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplaceSourceIP
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplaceSourceIP.description: The replace source IP of this multicast vlan.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRangeName.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRangeName
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRangeName.description: The name of multicast address range. When read, it shows NULL.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRangeState.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRangeState
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRangeState.description: This object is uesed to add or delete the specified multicast address range. when read it shows none(1); when set add(2) or delete(3),the swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRangeName should not be NULL. When set deleteAll(4), means delete all swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRangeName on this vlan.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanState.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanState
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanState.description: This object can be enabled or disabled IGMP-snooping multicast VLAN.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRowStatus.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRowStatus
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanUntagSourcePort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanUntagSourcePort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanUntagSourcePort.description: This object indicates the untagged member ports to add to the multicast VLAN.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRemapPriority.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRemapPriority
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRemapPriority.description: The priority value (0 to 7) to be associated with the data traffic to be forwarded on the multicast VLAN. When set to 8, the packet's original priority will be used.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplacePriority.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplacePriority
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplacePriority.description: Specifies that a packet's priority will be changed by the switch based on the remap priority. This flag will only take effect when remap priority is set.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTagMemberPort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTagMemberPort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTagMemberPort.description: This object indicates the port list of the tag member ports of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN.

swL2IGMPForwardingTable.name: swL2IGMPForwardingTable
swL2IGMPForwardingTable.description: The table containing current IGMP forwarding information which captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled. Note that the priority of IGMP table entries is lower than Filtering Table, i.e. if there is a table hash collision between the entries of IGMP Table and Filtering Table inside the switch H/W address table, then Filtering Table entry overwrite the colliding entry of IGMP Table. See swL2FilterMgmt description also.

swL2IGMPForwardingEntry.name: swL2IGMPForwardingEntry
swL2IGMPForwardingEntry.description: Information about current IGMP forwarding information which captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled.

swL2IGMPForwardingVid.name: swL2IGMPForwardingVid
swL2IGMPForwardingVid.description: This object indicates the Vid of individual IGMP table entry. It shows the Vid of IGMP report information captured on network.

swL2IGMPForwardingSrcIp.name: swL2IGMPForwardingSrcIp
swL2IGMPForwardingSrcIp.description: This object is identify source ip address.

swL2IGMPForwardingGroupAddr.name: swL2IGMPForwardingGroupAddr
swL2IGMPForwardingGroupAddr.description: This object is identify group ip address.

swL2IGMPForwardingPortMember.name: swL2IGMPForwardingPortMember
swL2IGMPForwardingPortMember.description: This object indicates which ports are belong to the same multicast group, in per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupTable.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupTable
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupTable.description: The table containing the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN group information

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupEntry.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupEntry
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupEntry.description: Information about current IGMP snooping multicast VLAN group.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupVid.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupVid
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupVid.description: This object indicates the Vid of IGMP snooping multicast VLAN group.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupRangeName.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupRangeName
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupRangeName.description: The name of multicast address range.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupHead.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupHead
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupHead.description: The head of multicast address range.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupTail.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupTail
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupTail.description: The tail of multicast address range.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupTable.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupTable
swIGMPSnoopingGroupTable.description: The table contains the current IGMP snooping group information captured by the device.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupEntry.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupEntry
swIGMPSnoopingGroupEntry.description: Information about the current IGMP snooping group information which has been captured by the device.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupVid.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupVid
swIGMPSnoopingGroupVid.description: This object indicates the VID of the individual IGMP snooping group table entry.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupGroupAddr.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupGroupAddr
swIGMPSnoopingGroupGroupAddr.description: This object identifies the group IP address which have been captured from the IGMP packet, on a per-VLAN basis.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupSourceAddr.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupSourceAddr
swIGMPSnoopingGroupSourceAddr.description: This object identifies the source addresses.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupIncludePortMap.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupIncludePortMap
swIGMPSnoopingGroupIncludePortMap.description: This object indicates the port list under INCLUDE mode.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupExcludePortMap.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupExcludePortMap
swIGMPSnoopingGroupExcludePortMap.description: This object indicates the port list under EXCLUDE mode.

swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupTable.name: swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupTable
swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupTable.description: The table contains the current IGMP snooping static group information captured by the device.

swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupEntry.name: swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupEntry
swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupEntry.description: Information about current IGMP snooping static group information captured by the device.

swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupVID.name: swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupVID
swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupVID.description: This object indicates the VID of the current IGMP snooping static group.

swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupIPaddress.name: swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupIPaddress
swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupIPaddress.description: This object indicates the current IGMP snooping static group IP address.

swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupMemberPortLis.name: swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupMemberPortList
swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupMemberPortLis.description: This object indicates the current IGMP snooping static group Member Portlist.

swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupRowStatus.name: swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupRowStatus
swL2IGMPSnoopingStaticGroupRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2TrafficSegTable.name: swL2TrafficSegTable
swL2TrafficSegTable.description: This table specifys the port just can forward traffic to the specific port list.

swL2TrafficSegEntry.name: swL2TrafficSegEntry
swL2TrafficSegEntry.description: A list of information specifies the port with its traffic forward list.

swL2TrafficSegPort.name: swL2TrafficSegPort
swL2TrafficSegPort.description: The port number of the logical port.

swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.name: swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts
swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.description: The port list that the specific port can forward traffic.

swL2IpLimitedMulticastTable.name: swL2IpLimitedMulticastTable
swL2IpLimitedMulticastTable.description: This entity's per-port Limited IP multicast address range table.

swL2IpLimitedMulticastEntry.name: swL2IpLimitedMulticastEntry
swL2IpLimitedMulticastEntry.description: A particular route to a particular destination, under a particular policy. Once an entry be built,it shouldn't be modified.That is,it just support create and delete action.

swL2IpLimitedMulticastPortIndex.name: swL2IpLimitedMulticastPortIndex
swL2IpLimitedMulticastPortIndex.description: A port to config the limited multicast address.

swL2IpLimitedMulticastHead.name: swL2IpLimitedMulticastHead
swL2IpLimitedMulticastHead.description: The head of multicast address range.

swL2IpLimitedMulticastTail.name: swL2IpLimitedMulticastTail
swL2IpLimitedMulticastTail.description: The tail of multicast address range.

swL2IpLimitedMulticastAccess.name: swL2IpLimitedMulticastAccess
swL2IpLimitedMulticastAccess.description: It allow you to permit or deny multicast range.

swL2IpLimitedMulticastState.name: swL2IpLimitedMulticastState
swL2IpLimitedMulticastState.description: Enable or disable limited multicast address for the chosen port.

swL2IpLimitedMulticastDelState.name: swL2IpLimitedMulticastDelState
swL2IpLimitedMulticastDelState.description: Enable or disable delete limited multicast address for the chosen port.

swL2IpLimitedMulticastRangeName.name: swL2IpLimitedMulticastRangeName
swL2IpLimitedMulticastRangeName.description: The name of multicast address range. When read, it shows NULL.

swL2IpLimitedMulticastRangeNameState.name: swL2IpLimitedMulticastRangeNameState
swL2IpLimitedMulticastRangeNameState.description: Add or delete the specified multicast address range. When read, it shows other(1); When set add(2) or delete(3), the swL2IpLimitedMulticastRangeName should be set also, and it should not be NULL. When set deleteAll(4), means delete all swL2IpLimitedMulticastRangeName on this port. And the set multicast range name value could be gotten in swL2LimitedMulticastAddressTable.

swL2LimitedMulticastAddressTable.name: swL2LimitedMulticastAddressTable
swL2LimitedMulticastAddressTable.description: A table contains the limited multicast address information.

swL2LimitedMulticastAddressEntry.name: swL2LimitedMulticastAddressEntry
swL2LimitedMulticastAddressEntry.description: The information of limited multicast address.

swL2LimitedMulticastAddressRangeName.name: swL2LimitedMulticastAddressRangeName
swL2LimitedMulticastAddressRangeName.description: The name of multicast address range.

swL2LimitedMulticastAddressHead.name: swL2LimitedMulticastAddressHead
swL2LimitedMulticastAddressHead.description: The head of multicast address range.

swL2LimitedMulticastAddressTail.name: swL2LimitedMulticastAddressTail
swL2LimitedMulticastAddressTail.description: The tail of multicast address range.

swL2VlanTable.name: swL2VlanTable
swL2VlanTable.description: A table containing current configuration information for each VLAN currently configured into the device by (local or network) management, or dynamically created as a result of GVRP requests received.

swL2VlanEntry.name: swL2VlanEntry
swL2VlanEntry.description: Information for a VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management, or dynamically created as a result of GVRP requests received.

swL2VlanIndex.name: swL2VlanIndex
swL2VlanIndex.description: The VLAN ID of the VLAN to be created. The range is 1 - 4094.

swL2VlanName.name: swL2VlanName
swL2VlanName.description: The name of the VLAN to be displayed.

swL2VlanType.name: swL2VlanType
swL2VlanType.description: The type of the VLAN to be displayed.

swL2VlanMemberPorts.name: swL2VlanMemberPorts
swL2VlanMemberPorts.description: A range of member ports to the VLAN.

swL2VlanStaticPorts.name: swL2VlanStaticPorts
swL2VlanStaticPorts.description: A range of static ports to the VLAN.

swL2VlanStaticTaggedPorts.name: swL2VlanStaticTaggedPorts
swL2VlanStaticTaggedPorts.description: Specifies the additional ports as tagged.

swL2VlanStaticUntaggedPorts.name: swL2VlanStaticUntaggedPorts
swL2VlanStaticUntaggedPorts.description: Specifies the additional ports as untagged.

swL2VlanForbiddenPorts.name: swL2VlanForbiddenPorts
swL2VlanForbiddenPorts.description: The set of ports which are prohibited by management from being included in the egress list for this VLAN. Changes to this object that cause a port to be included or excluded affect the per-port per-VLAN Registrar control for Registration Forbidden for the relevant GVRP state machine on each port. A port may not be added in this set if it is already a member of the set of ports in dot1qVlanStaticEgressPorts. The default value of this object is a string of zeros of appropriate length, excluding all ports from the forbidden set.

swL2VlanCurrentTaggedPorts.name: swL2VlanCurrentTaggedPorts
swL2VlanCurrentTaggedPorts.description: The set of ports which are transmitting traffic for this VLAN as tagged frames.

swL2VlanCurrentUntaggedPorts.name: swL2VlanCurrentUntaggedPorts
swL2VlanCurrentUntaggedPorts.description: The set of ports which are transmitting traffic for this VLAN as untagged frames.

swL2VlanAdvertisementState.name: swL2VlanAdvertisementState
swL2VlanAdvertisementState.description: Specifies the VLAN as able to join GVRP If this parameter is not set, the VLAN cannot be configured to have forbidden ports. This flag protocol VLAN is fixed to DISABLE.

swL2PVIDAutoAssignmentState.name: swL2PVIDAutoAssignmentState
swL2PVIDAutoAssignmentState.description: This object controls the PVID auto assigment state. If 'Auto-assign PVID' is disabled, PVID only be changed by PVID configuration (user changes explicitly). The VLAN configuration will not automatically change PVID. If 'Auto-assign PVID' is enabled, PVID will be possibly changed by PVID or VLAN configuration. When user configures a port to VLAN X's untagged membership, this port's PVID will be updated with VLAN X. In the form of VLAN list command, PVID is updated with last item of VLAN list. When user removes a port from the untagged membership of the PVID's VLAN, the port's PVID will be assigned with 'default VLAN'.

swL2dot1vProtocolGroupTable.name: swL2dot1vProtocolGroupTable
swL2dot1vProtocolGroupTable.description: A table that contains mappings from Protocol Templates to Protocol Group Identifiers used for Port-and-Protocol-based VLAN Classification.

swL2dot1vProtocolGroupEntry.name: swL2dot1vProtocolGroupEntry
swL2dot1vProtocolGroupEntry.description: A mapping from a Protocol Template to a Protocol Group Identifier.

swL2dot1vProtocolTemplateFrameType.name: swL2dot1vProtocolTemplateFrameType
swL2dot1vProtocolTemplateFrameType.description: The data-link encapsulation format or the 'detagged-frame-type' in a Protocol Template.

swL2dot1vProtocolTemplateProtocolValue.name: swL2dot1vProtocolTemplateProtocolValue
swL2dot1vProtocolTemplateProtocolValue.description: The identification of the protocol above the data-link layer in a Protocol Template. Depending on the frame type, the octet string will have one of the following values: For 'ethernet', 'rfc1042' and 'snap8021H', this is the 16-bit (2-octet) IEEE 802.3 Type Field. For 'llcOther', this is the 2-octet IEEE 802.2 Link Service Access Point (LSAP) pair: first octet for Destination Service Access Point (DSAP) and second octet for Source Service Access Point (SSAP).

swL2dot1vProtocolGroupId.name: swL2dot1vProtocolGroupId
swL2dot1vProtocolGroupId.description: Represents a group of protocols that are associated together when assigning a VID to a frame.

swL2dot1vProtocolGroupRowStatus.name: swL2dot1vProtocolGroupRowStatus
swL2dot1vProtocolGroupRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2dot1vProtocolPortTable.name: swL2dot1vProtocolPortTable
swL2dot1vProtocolPortTable.description: A table that contains VID sets used for Port-and-Protocol-based VLAN Classification.

swL2dot1vProtocolPortEntry.name: swL2dot1vProtocolPortEntry
swL2dot1vProtocolPortEntry.description: A VID set for a port.

swL2dot1vProtocolPort.name: swL2dot1vProtocolPort
swL2dot1vProtocolPort.description: The port number of the port.

swL2dot1vProtocolPortGroupId.name: swL2dot1vProtocolPortGroupId
swL2dot1vProtocolPortGroupId.description: Designates a group of protocols in the Protocol Group Database.

swL2dot1vProtocolPortGroupVid.name: swL2dot1vProtocolPortGroupVid
swL2dot1vProtocolPortGroupVid.description: The VID associated with a group of protocols for each port.

swL2dot1vProtocolPortRowStatus.name: swL2dot1vProtocolPortRowStatus
swL2dot1vProtocolPortRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2MulticastRangeTable.name: swL2MulticastRangeTable
swL2MulticastRangeTable.description: A table contains multicast address range information.

swL2MulticastRangeName.name: swL2MulticastRangeName
swL2MulticastRangeName.description: The name of multicast address range.

swL2MulticastRangeHead.name: swL2MulticastRangeHead
swL2MulticastRangeHead.description: The head of multicast address range.

swL2MulticastRangeTail.name: swL2MulticastRangeTail
swL2MulticastRangeTail.description: The tail of multicast address range.

swL2MulticastRangeState.name: swL2MulticastRangeState
swL2MulticastRangeState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2LoopDetectAdminState.name: swL2LoopDetectAdminState
swL2LoopDetectAdminState.description: This object indicates the loopback detection status for the system.

swL2LoopDetectInterval.name: swL2LoopDetectInterval
swL2LoopDetectInterval.description: This object indicates the interval value, the range is from 1 to 32767 seconds.

swL2LoopDetectRecoverTime.name: swL2LoopDetectRecoverTime
swL2LoopDetectRecoverTime.description: This object indicates the recover time, the range is from 60 to 1000000. The value of 0 disables the recover function.

swL2LoopDetectMode.name: swL2LoopDetectMode
swL2LoopDetectMode.description: This object indicates the loopback detection mode for the system.

swL2LoopDetectTrapMode.name: swL2LoopDetectTrapMode
swL2LoopDetectTrapMode.description: This object indicates the loopback detection trap mode for the system.

swL2LoopDetectPortTable.name: swL2LoopDetectPortTable
swL2LoopDetectPortTable.description: The table specifies the loopback detection function specified by port.
